      <tr>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign=top width='100' nowrap><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'><b>Venjenz</b></font></td>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Just moved to Ratraz to farm some coin, but thought I would share a tried and true method for these levels:</P><P><b>12-17:</b> Siren 2-spawn at -990, 1900 in OOT. They con indifferent and do not assist. At 12, you will get a blue per kill, which is 2 blue every 6 minutes, meaning you will level from 12-17 at about a level every 2 hours. </P><P>Spell lineup is:<BR>LifeDraw<BR>Engulfing<BR>Heat Blood<BR>Leach<BR>Dark Pact<BR>Focus Death<BR>Swap Slot<BR>Swap Slot</P><P>The beauty of this spot is that it takes one DoT and pet to kill these gimp mobs and you can spend 5 minutes each spawn maxing out neglected spell skills like Divinate and Evoke. With VE, you can also do some tanking for raising Def and 1HB. I always bring new casters here to get my skills maxed while getting good exp. Any caster class will do for those making alts. </P><P><b>17:</b> Single Aviak spawn in LR in SE corner. I do this to set up for 18-20. Spawn can be 16-20, but I do the single at 17 since a red con can give bad resists.</P><P><b>18-20:</b> Double aviak guard spawn in middle of LR. The break is only tough part and why I wait until 18, so none of the spawns will ever be red. For break, just pull lowest con with Darkness, Fear the add, sic pet on pull, Fear, DoT, DoT and re-Fear the add as it comes back. A little tanking may be needed, but pretty easy break. Last time I did it, I ended with 60% health, 30m and Jabaner was at 40% health. Like the sirens, 2 spawns on 6 minute timer with good Fear kite area = too easy.</P><P>Aviak Lineup:<BR>LifeDraw<BR>Engulfing Dark<BR>Heat Blood<BR>Heart Flutter<BR>Leach<BR>Dark Pact<BR>Mend Bones/VE<BR>Focus Death/Swap Slot</P><P>Aviak guards work real well up to about 22 when it slows down. With 20 pet, the double spawn towers are basically trivial and it is a level every 2 to 3 hours. Up to 24, you will still get a yellow about every 45 minutes. Plenty of things to do at these levels, but these spots have worked for me.</P><P><b>Venjenz</b></P><P>"...the darkest magic...my soul swims in it."</font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>blunte</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> For those with Luclin, I can't even consider hunting anywhere but Paludal Caverns from 6 to 28.</P><P>The exp there is, as someone put it, broken :).  It's that good.</P><P>The extreme south end of zone, near Shadeweaver's Thicket is low stuff, like level 6 and up.  Then as you move north there are tougher versions of the same creatures (shrooms and bugs, and note that bugs are social.)</P><P>Moving further north (toward the center of the zone, where the bandits are), you'll meet the Plergs.  They suck, and there's no good reason to hunt them.  They have a really nasty disease, drop crappy loot, and hit really hard.</P><P>Hunt bugs and shrooms until 16, then get in a bandit group (bandits are most easily accessible from Shadowhaven zone entrance.)</P><P>Loot at bandits is good, and exp is still unrivaled.</P><P>1 blue bubble per kill is common, and at worst you'll see about half a blue per kill if you have a couple of partners in your group.</P><P>My bard just went to level 22 in just under 22 hours of total playtime.  My beastlord and necro did it faster because they were able to solo all the way (the bard grouped about half the time.)</P><P>Loot stinks until you get to bandits, then it's pretty good.  If you solo, the loot is outstanding.</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Rukarrn</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Actually, the fiends aren't that bad. Diseased pet? Pfft. Use Mend Bones. Though it can be annoying if you get diseased before you get Cure Disease, but it's still not bad. As for the loot, the loot off the fiends is better than off the mushrooms and bugs. At least the fiends drop a lot of armor, and food too. Only problem with the fiends is knowing where to set up camp, as they do get rather annoying when starting to add. There is an alcove sort of in-between SH and Shadeweaver's with Plerg fiends. About 3 or 4 of them in there. I would set the pet at the bottom of the ramp, go up and pull the first one with Darkness, then run down past pet, sick pet, dot, fear, lifetap a couple times, and its dead. Also in this hallway there are 3 static mushroom spawns. Middle one seems to usually be higher. What I did was usually pull only 1 or 2 of the fiends from the alcove, then I'd smoke the shrooms (:P) in the hall. There is another room with Plerg fiends at the end of that shroom hall, but again, easy to get adds from there. I went to 18 in this hall, then moved to the ramp near SH and started pickin off some fiends there, as well as the static shroom spawn. Once I got to 20, I moved a bit further up the ramp. Actually, there is a hallway just over the bridge along that ramp where you can set up camp. The Patog fiends here are spread out fairly well. There is 1 spawn right at the mouth of the tunnel, one to the left, and one further along on the right. There is also a roamer. I was plowing through them fairly easily. Sometimes I would get 2 at a time, but those were fairly easily handled. Mind you I did have 190+ int at the time (now sitting at 197), so I had enough mana to handle 2 at once. Did 3 in a row once, and almost died too, but it was a blast. Will be much easier when I get ST at 24. :) I have to say though at 23 a lot of the fiends were LBlue to me, and I can't be bothered with grouping for the bandits (like I need a group :)), so I'm lookin for a new place. Didn't like SK too much, so I might head back to OT and see what's cookin there, or maybe LOIO. Who knows. Happy hunting. :)</P><P>Fanusno Fluffydeath<BR>23 Erudite Necromancer<BR>Haven of Heroes</P><P> </font></td>
